      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 248: 🟡 In the first branch (`!askedOnce \u0026\u0026 !showRationale`), you persist `PREF_NOTIF_PERM_ASKED \u003d true` *before* the user responds. If the user denies the system prompt, the next launch will fall into the `else` branch (permanently blocked path) instead of the `showRationale` branch, because `askedOnce` will be true and `showRationale` may still be true. The logic coupling between `askedOnce` and `showRationale` is fragile. Consider setting the pref only *after* the result is received (in `onRequestPermissionsResult`) to keep state consistent.",
      "revId": "be9897afc7dbb0a2f2495061cae160ca53e0bfd3",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
